<br>
I've seen too many people (Brecht, Temperance, Kerna, and several other bards/paladins) stuck at lvl 52 waiting and wanting their epic pieces to move on... attending the raids weekly to better their chances and even leading their own raids to get it done... its NOT a fun battle im sure.<br>
<br>
If you're level 50 and you need it you have a lot more time/opportunity to go on the vox/naggy raids (weekly on the norm/nightly due to patching) they, however, dont have as many opportunities unless they penalize themselves to be able to make the raids... you can still attend the raids without the penalties.  You can go and exp... take a night off to kill a dragon... go and exp... etc etc... they, however, have to refrain from leveling at all.  I didnt level past 52 for several reasons 1. I wanted a shot at the eyepatch 2. I wanted to be there fighting along Kerna until he got his book.<br>
<br>
but anyway...<br>
<br>
I've done 52 only for epic pieces... I've done 51-52 only for epic pieces... I've done 50+ only for epic pieces... I've had raids where there was NO level requirement... when I do the raids (if you've raided with me and payed attention to my loot rules posted) I often alter things slightly to make the odds better for the people involved giving everyone an opportunity to take advantage of what will best suit them.<br>
<br>
Just like with me giving the lvl 60 clerics who come along a shot at the eyepatch, or like tonight the pally a shot at the RBB... thats how I do it... I now post that on my threads... "Buffers who come along to help with the dragons who are too high to fight WILL be allowed in my randoms" (this is especially nice when the buffer is a lvl 60 cleric giving everyone lvl 56 res's after the fight) and as always if you dont like it... dont come /shrug<br>
<br>
I do the dragon raids for fun... yes I have always wanted to lead a Vox raid and "win" an eyepatch but I honestly have more fun seeing my friends and devoted raiders go home with the items they need/desire because thats what makes it worth it.<br>
<br>
I would give up any dragon loot item from Vox or Naggy to see half of the raiders I raid with regularly go home with something they need (especially the epics) <br>
<br>
I led the raid the other night and held the res stick for me... I've never held loot for myself before but I was only leading the raid because no one else was and it gave people an opportunity to get the items they desire without having to take on the hassle of leading the raid.... and plain and simple if they didnt like the rules they wouldnt be there.<br>
<br>
By you leaving the raid before it started you made the right choice... you were not happy with the loot rules so you left.  But it comes down to this "if you dont like the rules do it yourself" I cant think of any other way to say it.<br>
