<br>
Everyone starts out the same.  Some people just work harder to achieve what they have.  I'm sure there's a decent leader among you, so get leading.  Believe it or not, 'Uber' guilds don't cheat, exploit and farm to become 'Uber'.  They 'work for it'.<br>
<br>
If however you are content to stay sub-53 and go on endless Nag/Vox raids go for it.  Just stop complaining that you're lack of effort isn't rewarding you enough.<br>
<br>
Stanman111 - Everyone contributes, true.  Some (a LOT) more than others however.  We all stand an equal chance of getting killed? Not at all.  Lv 45 caster is much more likely to die than a lv 52 warrior.  Not taking into account player skill, class abilities, hit points, positioning, aggro management, etc...<br>
<br>
Oh and the 'fair loot rules'? What's the point of giving a pally book to a level 46 paladin that plays 6 hours a week and will almost certainly never finish their epic when a lv52 pally has attended countless raids to get the book so he can finish? It's called *realism*<br>
